		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Hello, new here, and need best recommandations.</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have been interested in NESMaker, yet I didn't feel like buying it after looking into the files, which is kind of preused. <br /><br />Can anyone recommend me the best software to start off? Obviously, Bunnyboy seems best by people's standard, and I am wondering if there's the best tool list to do, so I made a list if anyone could help me out:<br /><br />-Writing : Notepad ++<br /><br />-Music : Famitracker<br /><br />- Graphic : YY-CHR or Aseprite<br /><br />I am not sure if there is more, so helping me find more tools would be nice.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>dougeff</b> [ Sun Jun 17, 2018 6:57 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Hello, new here, and need best recommandations.</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />And NES Screen Tool. and it's RLE compression system.<br /><br />And I prefer asm6 to NESASM3. Some use ca65.<br /><br />And famitone2 to convert famitracker to a more game friendly music format.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>zzo38</b> [ Sun Jun 17, 2018 7:37 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Hello, new here, and need best recommandations.</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Another program for graphics is Damian Yerrick's &quot;8ted&quot; and &quot;8Name&quot; programs. There is also my own Farbfeld Utilities programs &quot;ffbit&quot; which can convert graphics into NES/Famicom format (and &quot;ff-uniq&quot; if you want to get rid of duplicate tiles).<br /><br />For text editing I use vim, although you can use any text editor.<br /><br />Another program for using is ppMCK, although that is intended for writing .NSF files rather than music for the game. Another program for music is Pently, which I believe is suitable to make music for a game, as well as for NSF.<br /><br />For assembler many prefer ca65 or asm6, although I still like NESASM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


