	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's realistic. There's a lot of information out there. If you want to use nesmaker you need to wait for its release. If you want to program on your own you can look at tutorials such as dougeff's  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://nesdoug.com/">https://nesdoug.com/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Either way it's going to take a while. Get to work and when you have a technical question that you can't solve you can ask here for clarification. But be ready to get responses like this if it's clear that you haven't been reading enough. This is a rewarding hobby that takes a lot of time from reading and trying things out yourself.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


